'''David Hattersly Warner''' (born [[July 29]], [[1940s|1941]], [[Wikipedia:Manchester|Manchester]], [[Wikipedia:United Kingdom|United Kingdom]]<ref name="Birth" />&mdash;died [[July 24]], [[2022]], [[Wikipedia:London|London]], United Kingdom) was an [[Wikipedia:English people|English]] actor.<ref name="Death" /> He was known for a wide variety of roles, including Spicer Lovejoy in [[Wikipedia:Titanic (1997 film)|''Titanic'']]<ref name="Birth" /> ([[1997]]) and multiple characters in the [[Wikipedia:Star Trek|''Star Trek'']] and [[Wikipedia:Doctor Who|''Doctor Who'']] franchises.<ref name="Death" /> For the ''[[Star Wars]]'' franchise, Warner voiced [[Grand General/Legends|Grand General]] [[Malcor Brashin]] in the [[2000]] [[LucasArts]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars: Force Commander]]''.<ref name="Force Commander">''[[Star Wars: Force Commander]]''</ref>

